<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900709-0095</DOCNO><DOCID>900709-0095.</DOCID><HL>   Hong Kong Legal Officer   Sentenced for Corruption</HL><DATE>07/09/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   FREST</CO><LP>   HONG KONG -- Despite pleas for leniency and promises offuture cooperation with government investigators, the formerchief of the commercial crime unit of Hong Kong's LegalDepartment was sentenced to eight years in prison forcorruption.   Charles Warwick Reid last month pleaded guilty to a chargeof possessing assets deemed disproportionate to his officialincome.</LP><TEXT>   At Friday's sentencing, Hong Kong's chief justice, Sir TiLiang Yang, ordered Mr. Reid to pay the local governmentHK$12.4 million ($1.6 million), the value of his assets whenhe was formally charged in March 1989. Mr. Reid has 28 daysto appeal the court's decision.   Chief Justice Yang allowed a two-year reduction of themaximum penalty of 10 years because of Mr. Reid's guilty pleaand his willingness to cooperate with the government.   Mr. Reid's lawyer, Anthony Corrigan, Queen's Counsel,argued that the court's leniency would elicit assistance fromthe defendant in bringing other corrupt government officialsand businessmen to trial.</TEXT></DOC>